### Database Models

#### [NEW] [core/models.py](file:///c:/Users/Omutooro/Desktop/Projects/Scheduler_V2/core/models.py)

| Model | Key Fields | Purpose |
|-------|-----------|---------|
| `Airline` | id, iata_code, icao_code, name, is_home_airline | Pre-seeded airline reference data |
| `Airport` | id, iata_code, icao_code, city_name | Pre-seeded airport reference data |
| `AircraftType` | id, code, name, category (wide_body/narrow_body/regional/turboprop), size_code (B-F) | Aircraft lookup |
| `FlightRequest` | id, airline_id, arrival_flight_number, departure_flight_number, aircraft_type_id, operation_type (turnaround/arrival/departure), season, year, arrival_time, departure_time, origin_id, destination_id, valid_from, valid_to, days_of_operation (bitmask), status | Core flight request. Turnarounds have two flight numbers (e.g. EK729 arrival, EK730 departure). Single operations use one. |
| `StandAllocation` | id, flight_request_id, stand_id, date, start_time, end_time | Stand timing derived from arrival_time → departure_time |
| `GateAllocation` | id, flight_request_id, gate_id, date, start_time, end_time | Gate closes 15min before departure to allow next airline |
| `CheckInAllocation` | id, flight_request_id, counter_start, counter_end, date, start_time, end_time | Counter assignments with sharing rules |

