### Seed Data

#### [NEW] [seed_data.py](file:///c:/Users/Omutooro/Desktop/Projects/Scheduler_V2/seed_data.py)

**Airlines** (IATA-ICAO format):
UR-UGD (Uganda Airlines), EK-UAE (Emirates), TK-THY (Turkish), KQ-KQA (Kenya Airways), QR-QTR (Qatar Airways), 7F-FJE (First Jet), WB-RWD (RwandAir), ET-ETH (Ethiopian), F2-XLK (Safarilink), G9-ABY (Air Arabia Abu Dhabi), TC-ATC (Air Tanzania), FZ-FDB (flydubai), MS-MSR (EgyptAir), XY-KNE (flynas), SN-BEL (Brussels Airlines), KL-KLM (KLM), 3T-TQQ (Tarco Air)

**Airports** (IATA code / city):
EBB/Entebbe, DXB/Dubai, FIH/Kinshasa, JNB/Johannesburg, NBO/Nairobi, ZNZ/Zanzibar, DAR/Dar es Salaam, JRO/Kilimanjaro, KGL/Kigali, LGW/London, ABV/Abuja, BOM/Mumbai, JUB/Juba, BJM/Bujumbura, MBA/Mombasa, BRU/Brussels, CAI/Cairo, IST/Istanbul, ADD/Addis Ababa, AMS/Amsterdam, SHJ/Sharjah, RUH/Riyadh, LLW/Lilongwe, DOH/Doha

**Aircraft Types** with size codes and wide-body flag:
B777 (Code E, wide), B789 (Code E, wide), A333 (Code E, wide), A338 (Code E, wide), B738 (Code C, narrow), A21N (Code C, narrow), B38M (Code C, narrow), CRJ9 (Code C, regional), DH8C (Code B, turboprop), C208 (Code A, turboprop)

**Airport Resources** (hardcoded for initial seed):
- Apron 1 (Nose-in): 8 stands (2-9). Stand 10 is Code B. Stands 5, 6, 7 can be subdivided.
- Apron 1 Extended (Remote, Nose-out): 6 stands (20-25), all Code C.
- 6 gates (1, 2A, 2B, 3A, 3B, 4) — 2B and 4 connected to boarding bridges (stands 5 and 6)
- 22 check-in counters (1-4 dedicated Uganda Airlines)

