### Business Logic

#### [NEW] [core/services/season.py](file:///c:/Users/Omutooro/Desktop/Projects/Scheduler_V2/core/services/season.py)
- Calculate last Sunday of March and last Saturday of October for any year
- Determine current season and season date ranges

#### [NEW] [core/services/allocation.py](file:///c:/Users/Omutooro/Desktop/Projects/Scheduler_V2/core/services/allocation.py)
- **Stand allocation**: Timing = arrival_time to departure_time. Match aircraft size code to stand code; wide-body preference for stands 5/6 (boarding bridges)
- **Gate allocation**: Bridge gates (2B, 4) preferred for wide-body. Gate closes 15min before departure for turnover.
- **Check-in counter rules**: Close 1hr before departure; 3hrs for wide-body, 2hrs for others; 5-7 counters for wide-body; Counters 1-4 prioritized for Uganda Airlines. **Sharing**: Airlines can start with fewer counters if there's a 30-min overlap window with a closing airline. Incoming airline must get at least 2 counters. Wide-body airlines start with at least 4 counters.
- **Conflict detection**: No overlapping allocations on same resource

#### [NEW] [core/services/schedule.py](file:///c:/Users/Omutooro/Desktop/Projects/Scheduler_V2/core/services/schedule.py)
- Generate daily flight list from flight requests based on date and days-of-operation
- Expand seasonal requests into daily occurrences

